<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-01-30T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-01-30T17:00:00-05:00" n="535" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d535">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.51/1377: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-01-30T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January 30,
                                        1922—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>4. Deliver following to President King—“I thank you for your message
                            received January 26th<note n="7" xml:id="d535fn7">Not printed.</note>
                            informing me that loan agreement has been approved by Liberian
                            legislature without amendment.<note n="8" xml:id="d535fn8">The agreement
                                was approved Jan. 23.</note> The matter is pending in Congress and I
                            trust that favorable action will soon be taken.”</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>